      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nationalism is a deeply divisive and often intensely political ideology, and its impact is rarely purely positive. When it emphasizes shared culture and identity, it can foster a sense of belonging and social cohesion. However, when it morphs into chauvinism, it becomes a dangerous force that justifies exclusion, conflict, and hostility toward other groups. Therefore, its manifestation determines whether it is a unifying force or a destructive one.",
