    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but youre saying \"true\" social cohesion comes from institutions and respect, which sounds like you're saying nationalism can never actually be the source of true cohesion. if even \"civic nationalism\" is just a way to avoid the \"dangerous\" side of it, isn't that basically saying any form of nationalism is inherently flawed or a problem to be managed?",
